<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Matthew Takara — civil & environmental engineering student and researcher at Carnegie Mellon University."
>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      I'm a civil and environmental engineering student at Carnegie Mellon University.
      My research sits at the intersection of environmental sensing, embedded systems, and
      data infrastructure — building systems that observe the physical world at scale.
    </p>
    <p>
      I've worked on multi-node sensing deployments using Jetson Orin Nano hardware,
      analog signal-conditioning chains for geophone arrays, and applied machine learning
      in industry. I'm comfortable moving between hardware constraints, signal processing,
      and the software layer above it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>About this site</h2>
    <p>
      Built with Astro — static HTML, system fonts, no JavaScript unless it earns its place.
      A later phase will self-host on a Raspberry Pi 5 and publish real wattage and
      grid carbon data to a <a href="/green">live dashboard</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
